<BaseLayout
  title="Residential Solar Panels Geelong & Torquay | Installation | EES"
  description="Expert residential solar panel installation in Geelong, Torquay and the Surf Coast. CEC accredited, designed for your home, backed by a 10-year workmanship warranty."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Residential Solar Systems</h1>
      <p>Solar panel installation designed around your home and energy profile.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Solar Designed for Your Home</h2>
      <p>
        Every home is different — roof orientation, shading, energy usage, and future plans all affect what solar system will perform best. We design each system around your specific property, not a generic template.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our process starts with a detailed assessment of your roof, energy bills, and goals. From there, we design a system that maximises self-consumption and delivers the best return on your investment.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Install</h2>
      <p>
        We use high-quality panels and inverters from manufacturers with strong warranties and proven performance in Australian conditions. Every component is selected for long-term reliability, not just the lowest price.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tier 1 solar panels</strong> — independently tested and rated for Australian conditions</li>
        <li><strong>Quality inverters</strong> — the component that converts DC power from your panels to AC power for your home</li>
        <li><strong>Optimised design</strong> — panel placement and string configuration designed for your specific roof</li>
        <li><strong>Full monitoring</strong> — see your generation and consumption in real time from your phone</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>System Sizes</h2>
      <p>
        The right system size depends on your energy consumption, roof space, and whether you plan to add a battery later.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>6.6 kW</strong> — suits smaller households with moderate energy use</li>
        <li><strong>10 kW</strong> — the most common size for a family home, maximises the federal STC rebate</li>
        <li><strong>13–15 kW</strong> — for larger homes, homes with pools, or households planning to add a battery, heat pump, or EV charger</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We'll recommend the right size during your consultation based on your actual usage data.
      </p>

      <h2>Rebates and Incentives</h2>
      <p>
        The federal government provides an upfront discount on solar installations through Small-scale Technology Certificates (STCs). This is applied as a point-of-sale discount — you don't need to claim it separately.
      </p>
      <p>
        Additional Victorian Government rebates may be available depending on your property and household income. As a Solar Victoria approved retailer, we can confirm your eligibility and handle the application process.
      </p>

      <h2>Installation Process</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Consultation</strong> — we assess your property, review your bills, and discuss your goals</li>
        <li><strong>Design</strong> — we design a system tailored to your roof and energy profile</li>
        <li><strong>Paperwork</strong> — we handle the rebate application, grid connection approval, and permits</li>
        <li><strong>Installation</strong> — our CEC-accredited electricians install the system, typically in one day</li>
        <li><strong>Commissioning</strong> — we test everything, connect monitoring, and walk you through the system</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Warranty and Support</h2>
      <p>
        Every installation comes with our <strong>10-year workmanship warranty</strong>, covering the installation itself — not just the products. If something goes wrong with how the system was installed, we fix it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Panel and inverter manufacturer warranties apply on top of this, typically 25 years for panels and 10–15 years for inverters.
      </p>

      <h2>Servicing Geelong, Torquay and the Surf Coast</h2>
      <p>
        We're a local team based in Moolap. We service Greater Geelong, Torquay, the Surf Coast, Bellarine Peninsula, Golden Plains, and wider regional Victoria. Because we're local, we're here for the long term — not a fly-in-fly-out installer.
      </p>

